# Frontend Patterns

## Project Structure

```
apps/frontend/src/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router pages and layouts
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout with providers
│   ├── page.tsx          # Home page
│   └── globals.css       # Tailwind directives
├── components/           # Reusable UI components
│   └── ui/               # shadcn/ui generated components
├── lib/                  # Utilities, API client, query keys
│   ├── api.ts            # Centralized fetch wrapper
│   └── utils.ts          # shadcn cn() helper
└── hooks/                # Custom React hooks (if needed)
```

## Data Fetching — TanStack Query

- ALL server data fetching MUST use TanStack Query hooks
- Wrap the app in `QueryClientProvider` (done in `app/layout.tsx` or a providers component)
- Use `useQuery` for GET requests, `useMutation` for POST/PUT/DELETE
- Define query keys as constants: `queryKeys.scenarios.list`, `queryKeys.scenarios.detail(id)`
- Invalidate related queries after mutations with `queryClient.invalidateQueries`
- Use `refetchInterval` or mutation invalidation for real-time updates — NOT manual polling with setInterval

```typescript
// Correct pattern
const { data, isLoading } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['scenarios', 'list'],
  queryFn: () => api.get('/api/scenarios'),
});

const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (data: RunScenarioDto) => api.post('/api/scenarios/run', data),
  onSuccess: () => {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['scenarios'] });
  },
});
```

## Forms — React Hook Form

- ALL forms MUST use React Hook Form with `useForm`
- Use zod schemas for validation with `@hookform/resolvers/zod`
- Connect form fields to shadcn/ui components via `Controller` or `register`
- Show validation errors inline using `formState.errors`

```typescript
const schema = z.object({
  type: z.enum(['success', 'validation_error', 'system_error', 'slow_request', 'teapot']),
  name: z.string().optional(),
});

const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof schema>>({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
  defaultValues: { type: 'success', name: '' },
});
```

## UI Components — shadcn/ui

- Use shadcn/ui components for all UI elements (Button, Card, Select, Badge, Input, Toast, etc.)
- Import from `@/components/ui/<component>`
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional Tailwind classes
- NEVER install Material UI, Chakra UI, Ant Design, or other component libraries

## Styling — Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes for ALL styling
- Use shadcn/ui CSS variables (defined in `globals.css`) for theme colors
- NEVER write inline `style={{}}` attributes
- NEVER create separate CSS files per component

## Component Guidelines

- Use functional components with TypeScript types
- One component per file, named export (except Next.js pages which need default export)
- Put "use client" directive only on components that need browser APIs, hooks, or interactivity
- Keep components small — extract logic into custom hooks
- Use loading states (`isLoading`, `isPending`) and error states from TanStack Query

## API Communication

- Backend runs at `http://localhost:3001` (configured via `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`)
- All API calls go through a centralized `api` utility in `lib/api.ts`
- NEVER hardcode the backend URL in components
